    "body" : "In reality you&#39;re probably going wrong arranging for <b>any</b> output, console or logging, when running tests!  The test method names, and assertion messages, of any failures should do everything you need.  Judging from your output it seems you want to monitor progress... but a set of unit tests should be fast (no run more than 15 s) and integration and end-to-end tests are going to need logger output (to a file) really, if at all..."
